04/05/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski visited the army watchtower at Dojran Lake on the Macedonian-Greek border Thursday (1 May), accompanied by Army Chief of General Staff Lt Gen Metodi Stamboliski and Border Brigade commander Brig Gen Gjorgi Bojadziev. During the inspection, Trajkovski said that, by year's end, the interior ministry will assume responsibly for border guarding and control in compliance with the Annual National Programme for NATO Membership. (MIA - 02/05/03)
